I just realized what was the problem. Adding `docu=` to `doccomment` will make the rule non-terminal e.g. there will be implicit regex match `/#<.*\n/` with the default priority and the priority of the `doccomment` production will be set to `20`. What you should do is to move your regex match to a terminal rule with raised priority:

```
doccomment : docu=doccomment_match;
doccomment_match: /#<.*\n/ {20};
```
So, this is expected behaviour after all :)

